definition.value: An organofluorine compound comprising salicylic acid having a 2,4-difluorophenyl group at the 5-position.

A N-sulfonylurea in which the sulfonyl group is attached to a 2-(methoxycarbonyl)phenyl group while a (4-methoxy-6-methyl-1,3,5-triazin-2-yl group replaces one of the amino hydrogens of the remaining urea group.
A naphthalenesulfonic acid that is naphthalene-1-sulfonic acid substituted by a phenylamino group at position 8.
A hydroxytoluene that is phenol substituted by amino and methyl groups at positions 2 and 4, respectively. It is a metabolite of disperse yellow 3.
An aminopyrimidine that is 2-amino-4-hydroxypyrimidine in which the hydrogen at position 5 is substituted by an ethoxycarbonyl group.
A carboxylic ester that results from the formal condensation between caprylic acid and the hydroxy group at position 6 of the glucosyl residue of sucrose.
An N-{5-[2-{4-[2-(dimethylamino)ethoxy]phenyl}-4-(pyridin-4-yl)-1H-imidazol-5-yl]-2,3-dihydro-1H-inden-1-ylidene}hydroxylamine in which the oxime group has Z configuration.
A monovalent inorganic anion that consists of phosphoric acid in which one of the three OH groups has been deprotonated.
A thiazolidinemonocarboxylic acid that is  1,3-thiazolidine substituted by geminal methyl groups at position 2 and a carboxy group at position 4 (the 4R stereoisomer).
An anthocyanin cation that is cyanidin(1+) carrying two beta-D-glucosyl residues at positions 3 and 5.
A zwitterion resulting from the transfer of a proton from the carboxy group to the nitrogen of 1-pyrroline-2-carboxylic acid; major species at pH 7.3.
An iodoarene that is 2-methylbenzene substituted by an iodo group at position 1.
A member of the class of  phenols that is phenol carrying an allyl group at position 2.
